    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Rev. D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. <persName role="author"
                    >Eckman</persName> at <placeName>Augusta</placeName></p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Augusta</placeName>
                <date>Augusta March 30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev. Mr. <addressee>Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">You will please insert the following<lb/> once in your periodical.—— </p>
            <p><add>In left margin: Long Primo</add> “At a meeting of the Board of Managers of the
                Congregation “B'nai–<lb/>Israel” of <placeName>Augusta Ga</placeName>, on
                    <date>February 23, 1852</date>( The following preamble<lb/> and resolution were
                unanimously passed—“Whereas the Rev. Dr<lb/>
                <persName>Julius Eckman</persName> having accepted the special invitation of
                this<lb/> congregation, and delivered a series of Lectures long to be
                remembered<lb/> with feelings of admiration—and whereas this congregation have<lb/>
                found in the Rev. Dr. a truly pious man—a profound scholar and a<lb/>
                gentleman........./</p>
            <p>Resolved—That a proper and suitable token expressive of our feelings be
                purchased—<lb/>—–A <sic>committy</sic> being appointed for <del>that</del> its
                selection—they reported<lb/> at a meeting of the Congregation on the <date>28<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> Feby</date>. that <persName>Lewis Levy</persName> and<lb/>
                <persName>Samuel Levy</persName> Esqrs had purchased a silver Goblet, as directed,
                and that<lb/> this Goblet and the sum of Fifty Dollars be presented to the Rev
                gentleman<lb/> the <sic>Committy</sic> further reported, that they had selected
                    <persName>Henry Morrison</persName> Esqr<lb/> to present the same....At a
                meeting of the Congregation on <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March</date>, it
                was/</p>
            <p>Resolved. That a <sic>committy</sic> be appointed to return the thanks of this
                congregation to<lb/>
                <persName>H. Morrison</persName> Esqr. for his able address delivered at the
                Presentation; and that<lb/>
                <persName>H. Morrison</persName> Esqr, and the Rev. Dr. <persName>Eckman</persName>
                be respectfully requested to furnish<lb/> the <sic>Committy</sic> with a copy of
                their respective addresses.</p>
            <p>Resolved That the whole of these proceedings be published in the Asmonean and<lb/> Occident.....<lb/>
                <add>In left margin: Small Pica</add> After the Rev. Dr. <persName>Eckman</persName>
                had delivered his last lecture, on<lb/> Sunday <date>March 7<hi rend="sup"
                    >th</hi></date> Mr <persName>Morrison</persName> arose and addressed him as
                follows.—– </p>
        </body>
